#compdef cogent
# =============================================================================
# cogent — Australian Data61/CSIRO's "Code and Proof
#          Co-Generation" language compiler — a Haskell-
#          implemented compiler for the Cogent
#          programming language, a restricted-subset
#          purely-functional language with LINEAR TYPES
#          designed to be COMPILED TO BOTH (1) efficient
#          C code AND (2) corresponding Isabelle/HOL
#          formal correctness proofs simultaneously,
#          enabling verified-by-construction systems
#          software whose C output is provably
#          equivalent to the high-level Cogent source.
#          Distinguishing from F* (Microsoft Research's
#          dependently-typed verification lang; emits
#          OCaml/F#/C but proofs are separate Z3 SMT
#          queries), Dafny (MS Research verification-
#          aware imperative; proofs via SMT), Coq (proof
#          assistant; manual proof scripts; OCaml
#          backend), Lean 4 (theorem prover; Lean
#          backend), Stainless (R756 EPFL Scala
#          verification via SMT), Bosque (R748 MS
#          Research SMT-backed regularized
#          programming), Hazel (R752 typed-holes live
#          programming), and Verona (R760 MS Research
#          concurrent ownership) by:
#            - CODE + PROOF CO-GENERATION — the
#              compiler emits BOTH the C
#              implementation AND the Isabelle/HOL
#              proof that the C is equivalent to the
#              Cogent source.  No other corpus
#              language emits both compiled artifact
#              and formal proof simultaneously from
#              the same source
#            - LINEAR TYPES via Dargent — Cogent's
#              type system is purely linear (each
#              variable used exactly once); Dargent
#              extension adds DATA LAYOUT
#              SPECIFICATIONS for precise C struct
#              layouts.  Critical for systems
#              programming where memory layout is
#              part of the API contract
#            - SEL4-AFFILIATED PROVENANCE — Cogent
#              was developed at Australian Data61/
#              CSIRO (Commonwealth Scientific and
#              Industrial Research Organisation), the
#              same lab that produced seL4 (the
#              first formally-verified general-
#              purpose microkernel) + their NICTA
#              predecessors.  Used in production for
#              verifying the BilbyFS file system
#              (the first Cogent-implemented + ISA-
#              verified Linux filesystem)
#            - MULTI-STAGE COMPILATION PIPELINE —
#              the compiler exposes every intermediate
#              representation as a CLI output target:
#              parse → typecheck → desugar → normal
#              → simplify → monomorphise → codegen.
#              Each stage has `--ast-*` (AST dump),
#              `--pretty-*` (pretty-print), `--deep-*`
#              + `--shallow-*` + `--scorres-*`
#              (Isabelle embeddings) targets
#            - ISABELLE/HOL EMBEDDINGS — multiple
#              theorem-prover embeddings generated:
#              * deep embedding (term-based,
#                generates type-correctness proofs)
#              * shallow embedding (logical, for
#                refinement proofs)
#              * shallow consts (constants only)
#              * shallow tuples (alternative tuple
#                representation)
#              * scorres (shallow correctness proof
#                between embedding levels)
#              * type-proof (Isabelle proof of type
#                correctness)
#              * mono-proof (monomorphisation proof)
#              * ac-install (AutoCorres install
#                theory)
#              * corres-setup + corres-proof
#                (c-refinement: prove generated C
#                refines Cogent source)
#              * normal-proof (normalisation proof)
#              * all-refine [COLLECTIVE] (shallow-to-
#                C complete refinement)
#            - QUICKCHECK ARTIFACTS — `-Q,
#              --quickcheck [COLLECTIVE]` generates
#              QuickCheck-compatible Haskell code +
#              tables for property-based testing of
#              the Cogent source + generated C
#            - HASKELL FFI GENERATION — `--hs-ffi`
#              emits both a `.hsc` module for types
#              + a `.hs` module for functions; lets
#              Haskell programs call into Cogent-
#              generated C code with type-safe
#              bindings
#            - LLVM EXPERIMENTAL BACKEND — `--llvm`
#              enables an alternative LLVM IR
#              backend; less mature than the C
#              backend but useful for research on
#              compiler verification
#            - DOCGENT — `--docgent` generates HTML
#              documentation from Cogent source
#              code's structured comments (analogous
#              to Haddock for Haskell, Doxygen for
#              C++)
#            - REPL via -i — `cogent -i / --repl`
#              starts an interactive Cogent
#              expression evaluator; useful for
#              learning the language semantics
#              without setting up the full proof
#              infrastructure
#            - DEBUG DUMP FLAGS — `--ddump-smt`
#              (verbose SMT-solving), `--ddump-tc`
#              (typechecking internals), `--ddump-
#              tc-ctx`, `--ddump-tc-filter <KEYS>`
#              (filtered dumps; gen|sol|post|tc),
#              `--ddump-to-file <FILE>` for compiler-
#              engineering work
#            - FEATURE TOGGLES — ~50 `--f*` /
#              `--fno-*` flag pairs for fine-grained
#              control over compilation behavior:
#              undefined-behavior checks, struct
#              flattening, function-call-as-macro
#              expansion, intermediate-variable
#              generation, normal-form selection
#              (anf/knf/lnf), purity attributes,
#              pretty-printing details, etc.
#            - ARCHITECTURE TARGET — `--arch arm32`
#              (default) | `x86_64` | `x86`; affects
#              word-size + pointer-size assumptions
#              in generated C code
#            - DARGENT WORD SIZE — `--fdargent-word-
#              size {8,16,32,64}` configures the
#              base word size when Dargent layout
#              specifications are used; matches
#              target architecture's natural word
#              size
#            - LIBGUM RUNTIME — `--libgum-dir` prints
#              the directory containing libgum (the
#              Cogent runtime library); set via
#              COGENT_LIBGUM_DIR environment variable
#            - COLLECTIVE COMMANDS — convenience
#              flags that compose multiple
#              generation steps:
#              * `-C, --c-refinement` — all files
#                for C refinement proof
#              * `-F, --functional-correctness` —
#                all files for functional correctness
#                proof
#              * `-A, --all` — generate everything
#              * `-Q, --quickcheck` — QuickCheck
#                artifacts
#            - 177+ STARS ON au-ts/cogent — research-
#              project pace; backed by Data61/CSIRO +
#              the Australian Trustworthy Systems
#              group (UNSW + Data61); GPL-2 licensed
#          Used by: formal-methods research groups
#          studying code-and-proof co-generation,
#          PhD students at UNSW + Data61 +
#          collaborating universities studying
#          verified systems software, the BilbyFS
#          verified Linux filesystem project, and
#          curiosity-driven verification engineers
#          interested in producing both code and
#          proof from a single source.
#
# Author:  Data61 (Commonwealth Scientific and
#          Industrial Research Organisation), the
#          Trustworthy Systems group at UNSW
#          Australia, and collaborators since 2015.
#          Repository at au-ts/cogent (the
#          "trustworthy systems Australia" GitHub
#          organization).  Project homepage at
#          trustworthy.systems/projects/TS/cogent.pml
# Source:  https://github.com/au-ts/cogent
#          https://github.com/au-ts/cogent/blob/master/cogent/Main.hs
#          https://github.com/au-ts/cogent/blob/master/cogent/src/Cogent/Flags.hs
#          https://github.com/au-ts/cogent/blob/master/cogent/src/Cogent/Compiler.hs
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; `cogent -?` or
#          `cogent -h [VERBOSITY=0..4]` shows help
