# WHY COGENT IS A DISTINCTIVE 125th-LANGUAGE ENTRY
# (POST-TRIFECTA):
#
#   Cogent occupies a unique position in the cross-
#   language taxonomy because it is the ONLY
#   language among the corpus's 124 existing
#   language slots that EMITS FORMAL CORRECTNESS
#   PROOFS ALONGSIDE COMPILED CODE FROM A SINGLE
#   SOURCE.  Every other verification-oriented
#   language in the corpus separates code emission
#   from proof emission:
#     * Coq/Lean/Idris/Agda — proof artifacts;
#       limited code emission
#     * F*/Dafny/Stainless/Bosque — code emission;
#       proofs are SMT solver queries (ephemeral,
#       not artifacts)
#     * Hazel — live program semantics; no
#       independent proof artifact
#     * Verona/Neut/Ante — compiled code with
#       type-system safety guarantees; no separate
#       Isabelle/HOL proof artifact
#
#   Cogent INVERTS THIS by treating the Isabelle
#   formal proof as a FIRST-CLASS COMPILATION
#   ARTIFACT alongside the C output.  When you run
#   `cogent --all-refine src.cogent`, you get BOTH
#   `out.c` AND `out_AllRefine.thy` (an Isabelle
#   theory proving the C refines the Cogent
#   source).
#
#   Distinguishing features in the broader cross-
#   language landscape:
#
#     1. CODE + PROOF CO-GENERATION — see above
#
#     2. LINEAR TYPES AS CORE FEATURE — Cogent's
#        entire type system is linear; this aligns
#        naturally with the Isabelle separation
#        logic embedding (separation logic + linear
#        types both treat resource consumption
#        explicitly)
#
#     3. SEL4 LINEAGE — Data61/CSIRO is also the
#        home of seL4, the first formally-verified
#        general-purpose microkernel.  Cogent
#        inherits the seL4 team's verification
#        toolchain (Isabelle/HOL + AutoCorres) and
#        applies it to user-space systems software
#
#     4. PRODUCTION USAGE in BILBYFS — Cogent is
#        not a toy language; it has been used to
#        implement BilbyFS, a verified Linux
#        filesystem
#
#     5. MULTI-EMBEDDING ISABELLE PROOFS — Cogent
#        emits BOTH a DEEP embedding (term-based
#        for type-correctness proofs) AND a
#        SHALLOW embedding (logical, for refinement
#        proofs) for the same source program; the
#        SCORRES embedding then proves they
#        correspond.  Most verification systems
#        commit to one embedding style; Cogent
#        leverages multiple
